SIMPLE: suffix
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suffix
<hw>Suf"fix</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>suffixus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>suffigere</ets> to fasten on, to
affix; <ets>sub</ets> under + <ets>figere</ets> to fix: cf. F.
<ets>suffixe</ets>. See <er>Fix</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A letter,
letters, syllable, or syllables added or appended to the end of a word
or a root to modify the meaning; a postfix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>A subscript mark, number, or
letter. See <er>Subscript</er>, <pos>a.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suffix</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Suffix
<hw>Suf*fix"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Suffixed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Suffixing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To add or annex to the
end, as a letter or syllable to a word; to append.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suffixion</ent>⟦br⟧
